r Cromwell: the unknowable, the inconstruable, the probably indefeasible Master Cromwell.Next day the king sends for him. He supposes it is to berate him for failing to get More to take the oath. \x{2018}Who will accompany me to this fiesta?\x{2019} he enquires. \x{2018}Master Sadler?\x{2019}As soon as he enters the king's presence, Henry gestures with a peremptory sweep of his arm for his attendants to clear a space, and leave him alone in it. His face is like thunder. \x{2018}Cromwell, have I not been a good lord to you?\x{2019}He begins to talk \x{2026} gracious, and more than gracious \x{2026} own sad unworthiness \x{2026} if fallen short in any particular begs most gracious pardon \x{2026}He can do this all day. He learned it from Wolsey.Henry says, \x{2018}Because my lord archbishop thinks I have not done well by you. But,\x{2019} he says, in the tone of one misunderstood, \x{2018}I am a prince known for my munificence.\x{2019} The whole thing seems to puzzle him. \x{2018}You are to be Master Secretary. Rewards shall follow. I do not understand why I have not done this long ago. But tell me: when it was put to you, about the lords Cromwell that once were in England, you said you were nothing to them. Have you thought further?\x{2019}\x{2018}To be honest, I never gave it another thought. I wouldn't wear another man's coat, or bear his arms. He might rise up from his grave and take issue with me.\x{2019}\x{2018}My lord Norfolk says you enjoy being low-born. He says you have devised it so, to torment him.\x{2019} Henry takes his arm. \x{2018}It would seem convenient to me,\x{2019} he says, \x{2018}that wherever we go \x{2013} though we shall not go far this summer, considering the queen's condition \x{2013} you should have rooms provided for you next to mine, so we can speak whenever I need you; and where it is possible, rooms that communicate directly, so that I need no go-between.\x{2019} He smiles towards the courtiers; they wash back, like a tide. \x{2018}God